parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, resulting in loss of power steering and brakes, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls after filling up with gas
the engine dies while driving
the vehicle loses power steering and brakes
the vehicle stalls at intersections or while merging with traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall, resulting in loss of power steering and brakes, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine dies while driving
the vehicle loses power
the engine stalls at intersections or while merging with traffic
the engine makes a knocking or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, resulting in loss of power steering and brakes, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's computer system misreads fuel levels
the engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle stalls at intersections or while merging with traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission console shift lever stays in Park
the console shift lever will not go into Reverse
the vehicle will not shift out of Park
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the engine shuts off without warning
the vehicle jerks or hesitates while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETC can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The Electronic Throttle Control (ETC) indicator symbol appears on the warning lamp
the vehicle shakes or stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCM/ECM can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off without warning
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the engine runs rough or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issues with the gas tank or fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power after filling up the gas tank
gas odors coming from the muffler.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank assembly can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off, leading to a loss of power steering and increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at low speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off after refueling
often multiple times; the vehicle sputters or dies at low speeds or when stopped at traffic lights; the vehicle loses power steering; the fuel pump works fine
but the vehicle still stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies after filling the gas tank
often when driving at low speeds or when stopped at a light. The vehicle may restart after a short period
but the problem persists.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vapor recovery system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies after filling the gas tank
often when driving at low speeds or when stopped at a light. The vehicle may restart after a short period
but the problem persists.
